**Issue:** React Hydration Mismatch - Nested `<html>/<body>` elements

## Problem Analysis
- Root layout (app/layout.tsx) renders `<html><body>` ✓
- Locale layout (app/[locale]/layout.tsx) ALSO renders `<html><body>` ❌
- Next.js App Router violation: Only root layout should define document structure
- Result: Nested HTML elements cause hydration mismatch

## Solution Applied
Remove `<html>` and `<body>` wrapper from LocaleLayout, keeping only providers and content wrapper.

## Files Modified
1. `src/app/[locale]/layout.tsx` - Remove nested HTML structure
2. `src/app/layout.tsx` - Update to handle locale-aware attributes

